The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques for keyphrase and summary extraction, which are commonly studied in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The use of dependency graphs and deep learning-based dependency parsers also suggests a potential fit with the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses applications to interactive content retrieval, which could fall under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
